com.communote.server.api.core.property

Class StringPropertyFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.communote.server.api.core.property.StringPropertyFilter

  • public class StringPropertyFilter
extends Object
    This filter allows fetching Propertyable entities which have a certain property or don't have a specific property. By omitting the value it is also possible to filter for entities which have (or don't have) properties with a given group and key but an arbitrary value.
    Author:
    Communote GmbH - http://www.communote.com/

      • isInclude

        public boolean isInclude()
        Returns:
        whether an entity only matches if it has or does not have a property with the key group, key and value. Defaults to true and thus the entity needs have the property.

      • setInclude

        public void setInclude(boolean include)
        Set whether to only match an entity if it has or does not have a property with the key group, key and value. The value of the property can be omitted to filter only for properties by their group and key. By default the entity needs to have the property.
        Parameters:
        include - true to require that the property is assigned

      • setKeyGroup

        public void setKeyGroup(String keyGroup)

        Parameters:
        keyGroup - the group

      • setPropertyKey

        Parameters:
        key - the property key

      • setPropertyValue

        public void setPropertyValue(String value)
        Set the value of the property which should or should not be assigned to an entity.
        Parameters:
        value - the value of the property. Can be null to allow arbitrary values and thus, filter for entities which have or don't have properties with the given group and key.
